    <!-- EN: #1/3 Razor shard study report -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.0.label>#1/3 刀锋碎片研究报告</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.0.label>
    <!--
        EN: Material properties of recently aquired archotechnology\n\nSubject: {PAWN_nameDef}\n\nAbstract:\nThis report details observations from Subject {PAWN_nameDef} regarding the visible properties of the aquired shard. The shard is equivalent in physical properties to the ones observed earlier, however this one is way larger in size. One side also appears to be incredibly sharp, calculations showing it to be mere nanometers in length. Any further observations yielded nothing of it's other properties. It is advised we wait for any activity from the object.\n\nObservations:\n{PAWN_nameDef} Reported morphological identity to other archotechnological shards, disregarding it's size.\nItem's sharpness was noted.\nCalculations show that the sharp side measures multiple nanometers in length.\nNo physical changes were observed post-contact.\n\nFindings:\nOnly the item's extraordinary sharpness is noted.\n\nDiscussion:\nThese finding suggests a potential existence of a mechanism responsible for the item's anomalous sharpness. Since no other activity was observed, we suggest that either the item hasn't entered it's active state yet, or that the activity is not observable by any available means.\n\nRecommendations:\nFurther experimentation/waiting is required. Additional tests with {PAWN_nameDef} and potentially other subjects are recommended to explore the potential of item's physical properties.
    -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.0.text>新近获得的超凡智能材料的特性\n\n对象 {PAWN_nameDef}\n\n摘要：\n本报告详细描述了对象{PAWN_nameDef}对获得碎片可见属性的观察结果。这块碎片的物理特性与之前观察到的碎片相同，但该碎片的尺寸要大得多。其中一面似乎还特别锋利，计算显示其宽度仅为数纳米。任何进一步的观察都没有发现其他特性。建议我们等待该物体的任何活动。\n\n现象：\n{PAWN_nameDef}报告该异常除大小外与一般碎片无异。\n注意到物体的锋利。\n计算表明其锋利一边的宽度仅有数纳米。\n接触后碎片的物理性质未发生改变。\n\n发现：\n只注意到物品异常锋利。\n\n讨论：\n这些发现表明，可能存在一种机制，导致了物品的异常锐利。由于没有观察到其他活动，我们认为要么该物品尚未进入活动状态，要么该活动无法通过任何现有手段观察到。\n\n建议：\n需要进一步实验/等待。建议对{PAWN_nameDef}和可能的其他对象进行更多测试，以探索项目物理特性的潜力。</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.0.text>
	
    <!-- EN: Razor shard -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.AnomalyLabel>刀锋碎片</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.AnomalyLabel>
    <!-- EN: A piece of dark archotechnology resembling the common shards, although this one seems to be much sharper, allowing it to cut through almost any material with ease, at the cost of having effects on the wielder's health -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.AnomalyDesc>一块与普通碎片相似的暗黑超凡碎片，不过这块碎片似乎要锋利得多，使其几乎可以轻松切割任何材料，但代价是持有人的健康。</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.AnomalyDesc>
    <!-- EN: #2/3 Razor shard study report -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.label>#2/3 刀锋碎片研究报告</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.label>
    <!--
        EN: Newly observed effects on colonist's health\n\nAbstract:\nThis report details observations concerning the newly discovered biological effects on the razor shard's wielder. Following its prolonged use, the wielder started to show symptoms not associated with any infection or disease. The pawn seems to be losing in constitution, becoming more pale and fragile, however at the same time more nimble, showing increase in manipulation and general flexibility. The pawn's organism also doesn't seem to have any immune reaction to this illness, suggesting it to be caused by a malfunction in the body itself. Given this observation, continued experimentation with the razor shard should be proceeded with caution. Further investigation into the shard's properties and its impact on colonists' health is warranted.\n\nObservations:\nFollowing the use of razor shard, a numerous symptoms were observed in the wielder.\nThe severity of those symptoms appears to be proportional to the time spent wielding the shard.\n\nDiscussion:\nThese findings suggest a potential unobservable force which both affects colonist's health and maintains shard's properties.\n\nRecommendations:\nGiven the potential detrimental effects, continued experimentation with the razor shard should be undertaken with caution, however further analysis of the shard's inner workings and its potential use is recommended.
    -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.text>新发现异常对殖民者健康的影响\n\n摘要：\n本报告详细介绍了有关新发现的刀锋碎片对持有者的生理影响的观察结果。在长期使用后，持有者开始出现与任何感染或疾病无关的症状。小人的体质似乎在下降，变得更加苍白和脆弱，但同时也更加灵活，显示出操作能力和一般灵活性的增强。小人似乎对这种疾病没有任何免疫反应，这表明它是由身体机制本身失灵引起的。鉴于这一观察结果，继续使用刀锋碎片进行实验时应谨慎行事。有必要进一步调查刀锋碎片的特性及其对殖民者健康的影响。\n\n现象：\n使用刀锋碎片后，使用者会出现许多症状。\n这些症状的严重程度似乎与使用碎片的时间成正比。n\n讨论：\n这些发现表明，有一种潜在的不可观测的力量既能影响殖民者的健康，又能保持碎片的特性。\n\n建议：\n鉴于潜在的有害影响，继续使用刀锋碎片进行实验应谨慎从事，但建议进一步分析碎片的内部构造及其潜在用途。</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.1.text>
	
    <!-- EN: Razor shard -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.AnomalyLabel>刀锋碎片</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.AnomalyLabel>
    <!-- EN: A piece of dark archotechnology resembling the common shards, although this one utilizes mechanites to reconstruct itself and maintain it's edge using biological resources taken from the wielder, which allows it to cut through almost any material with ease, at the cost of having considerable effects on the health -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.AnomalyDesc>一块与普通碎片相似的暗黑超凡碎片，使用纳米机械从持有者体内获取组织进行自我重构以保持锋利度，使其几乎可以轻松切割任何材料，但代价是持有人的健康。</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.AnomalyDesc>
    <!-- EN: #3/3 Razor shard study report -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.label>#3/3 刀锋碎片研究报告</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.label>
    <!--
        EN: Theory Regarding the mechanism behind Razor Shard\n\nSubject: {PAWN_nameDef}\n\nAbstract:\nThis report presents a novel theory proposed by Subject {PAWN_nameDef} regarding the mechanism behind razor shard. Subject suggests that the shard might be infused with mechanites akin to a monosword, which seems to have properties somewhat identical to the shard. This theory is based on a recent observation from the wielder, during which the shard's use has led to one of it's parts breaking off, after which it seemed to reconstruct the missing part. This has also led to further progress in the pawn's illness, suggesting that the shard takes materials necessary for reconstruction directly from the body. Lack of bodily resources such as proteins seems to be the cause of observed symptoms. Because of that, we have suggested a way to counteract shard's effects with medication. As a result of this observation, the anomaly associated with the shard has been classified as Paritally Safe.\n\nHypothesis:\nFollowing the prolonged use of the razor shard, {PAWN_nameDef} has proposed a theory concerning the item. Subject suggest the shard utilizes it's own mechanites and subject's bodily resources to reconstruct it's edge. This interaction has various effects on the body, mainly decrease in constitution and increase in flexibility.\n\nProposed Mechanism:\n{PAWN_nameDef}'s theory suggests that mechanites inside of the shard can get into the wielder's body, after which they take and repurpose various organic resources. This change in physiology, in turn, would explain the observed changes in constitution.\n\nOutcome:\nBased on information gained during this observation, {PAWN_nameDef} has successfully classified the anomaly associated with razor shard as Partially Safe.\n\nConsiderations:\nThe potential validity of Subject's theory requires further investigation. Because the shard only exhibits activity when in direct contact with the pawn, no risk is associated with it.\n\nRecommendations:\nDisregard: Given the potential consequences related to the shard's prolonged use, ignoring it may be a viable course of action.\nControlled Use: Alternatively, considering that the item's properties can be extremely useful, continued use of the shard under some form of control could offer significant advantages in our settlement's security. This approach, however, necessitates thorough risk assessment and the development of safety protocols to safeguard colonists' well-being.
    -->
	<AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.text>关于刀锋碎片的理论\n\n对象：{PAWN_nameDef}\n\n摘要：\n本报告介绍了对象{PAWN_nameDef}就刀锋碎片背后的机制提出的新理论。对象认为，刀锋碎片可能被注入了类似于单分子剑的纳米机械，因此其特性与单分子剑部分相同。这一理论的依据是持有者最近的一次观察，在使用过程中，碎片的刀锋出现了部分崩裂，随后它似乎又重建了缺失的部分。这也导致小人的病情进一步恶化，表明碎片直接从身体中获取了重建所需的材料。蛋白质等身体资组织的缺乏似乎是观察到的症状的原因。因此，我们提出了一种用药物抵消碎片影响的方法。根据这一观察结果，与碎片相关的异常已被分类为 “准安全”。\n\n假说：\n在长期使用刀锋碎片后，{PAWN_nameDef}提出了有关该物品的理论。对象认为，碎片使用纳米机械和对象的身体组织来重建其刀锋。这种作用会对身体产生各种影响，主要是降低体质和增加灵活性。\n\n拟提出机制：\n{PAWN_nameDef}的理论认为，碎片中的纳米机械可以进入持有者的身体，然后它们会获取各种有机资源并重新利用。这种生理变化反过来又解释了所观察到的体质变化。\n\n现象：\n根据本次观察获得的信息，{PAWN_nameDef}已成功将与刀锋碎片相关的异常分类为部分安全。\n\n审议：\n对象理论的潜在正确性需要进一步研究。因为碎片只有在与小人直接接触时才会表现出活动，所以不会有任何风险。n\n建议：\n无视： 考虑到长期使用碎片的潜在后果，忽略它可能是一种可行的做法。\n受控使用： 另一方面，考虑到该异常的可能非常有用，在某种形式的控制下继续使用刀锋碎片可能会为我们定居点的安全带来巨大优势。不过，这种方法需要进行全面的风险评估，并制定安全协议，以保障殖民者的安全。</AE_ShardMonosword.comps.CompAEStudyUnlocks.studyNotes.2.text>

